	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Drag</b> [ Wed Nov 21, 2012 11:00 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: NES DLC idea</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I think it'd be more reliable to do it the old-fashioned 8-bit computer way of using cassette tapes. If you need sample code to read/write cassette tape data, Excite Bike and Wrecking Crew have it built-in (look at the load/save options in edit mode, on the NES version). The DLC can be read off of the tape and stored on battery-backed RAM inside the cart for convenience.<br /><br />You could also use the FDS, but you have to deal with load times. That and I don't think anyone makes FDS disks anymore, let alone devices to write to them.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

