	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I like the idea, but the problem I see with using the Zapper to transfer data is that from what I understand, (probably already mentioned) that it's only going to work with a 15khz H refresh rate monitor (CRT TV and not much else).  Sounds like it's not a problem for some of the Famiclone lightguns though.<br /><br />I wonder if the Zapper VCR saving idea would work, that would be cool.<br /><br />BTW, this really should've been on the nesdev main page:<br /><img src="http://nesdev.com/tapedrv.PNG" alt="Image" /><br />by sepi, this was confirmed to work with Excitebike, etc. recording to a PC soundcard (not sure if he tried tape).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


